	<p>This credit cannot be claimed by those who are married and file separately.  Nor can the Hope Scholarship Tax Credit and the Lifetime Learning Tax Credit be used in the same year for the same individual.</p>

	<h3>Calculating Your Tax Credit</h3>

	<p>This credit applies only for tuition and fees at accredited colleges that are approved by the Department of Education.  If the school offers FFELP loans, it is an accredited college approved by the Department of Education.  Cost of books, supplies, and equipment may be included only if they must be paid to the school in order to enroll.  Room and board, transportation, and living expenses may not be included in the credit you claim.  If a student receives a scholarship for full tuition, this credit cannot be used.</p>

	<p>The credit is a maximum of $1,800 per year <em>per student</em>. (Thus a family with 2 children in college can use the Hope Scholarship Tax Credit twice.) The first $1,200 of qualified expenses is covered at 100%.</p>

